{"word":"πόθι","slug":"πόθι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πόθι</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:poetically'>poet.</a> for <a href='S:ποῦ'><el>ποῦ</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b>interrog. <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <i>where?</i> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>;—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>πόθι Νύσας</el>; <i>in what part</i> of Nysa? <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>for <el>ποῖ</el>; <i>whither?</i> <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}